<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n42187b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42187b">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42187b"> 187(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ghost shirt father</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&lsquo;You have a lot of girls standing against a wall, one of them being the mother of the others. She tells them to go and see if father&apos;s shirt&apos;s dry (the shirt being a girl in white, standing at a distance). They go in turn to see if it is dry &amp; each time <mark>the &ldquo;ghost&rdquo; in father&apos;s shirt</mark> catches one.&rsquo; <small> Norman Douglas, <a name="NDLS1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#NDLS1"><cite title="source">London Street Games</cite></a>, 2nd ed. (May 1931) 24</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
